snippet.title: Tour the battleship USS Missouri
snippet.description: From World War II, through Korea, the Cold War, and Desert Storm, the Missouri served her country for 48 years. Take a photo tour of this incredible battleship.

snippet.title: Say it with a USS Enterprise ring
snippet.description: Jeweler Gino Arizmendi has made some beautiful geek-themed pieces. One of his latest is a stunning ring that will make "Star Trek" fans' hearts go pitter-patter.

snippet.title: A tour of the legendary USS Missouri (pictures)
snippet.description: Tour the Mighty Mo, an Iowa-class battleship that fought in WWII, Korea, Desert Storm, and on whose decks the peace treaty between the US and Japan was signed.

snippet.title: USS Washington avoids the ax -- for now (pictures)
snippet.description: The ship is part of an aging class of nuclear-powered aircraft carriers in the US Navy that may soon be on the way out due to budgetary pressures.

snippet.title: The USS Langley and the dawn of the aircraft carrier
snippet.description: In March 1922, the U.S. Navy launched a bold experiment that really took off. Behold its first-ever aircraft carrier.

snippet.title: With the USS Langley, aircraft carriers took off (photos)
snippet.description: Aircraft carriers weren't always the high-tech marvels they are today. In fact, the U.S. Navy's very first one wasn't even a carrier at first.

snippet.title: USS Enterprise: Nuclear power meets aircraft carrier (photos)
snippet.description: Fifty years ago today, the U.S. Navy commissioned the world's first nuclear-powered carrier. It's now the oldest ship in the U.S. fleet, but retirement looms.

snippet.title: Space, military history abounds on USS Hornet (photos)
snippet.description: Now docked in Alameda, Calif., the aircraft carrier over the years was a stalwart of World War II operations, Cold War balance of power, and the U.S. space program.

snippet.title: All 550 pounds of Lego USS Intrepid docks in NY
snippet.description: The biggest Lego model you've probably ever seen is unveiled aboard the real, 30,000-plus ton aircraft carrier.

snippet.title: USS Enterprise will take your calls
snippet.description: Star Trek ship becomes a land line.
